\emph{When using the \LaTeX{} high-level font
commands, the \emph{proper} use of italic
corrections is \emph{automatically} taken
care of}. Only \emph{very seldom} one has to
help \LaTeX{} by adding \verb=\nocorr=; e.g.,
to avoid \textit{f}\textsubscript{1} and
instead get \textit{f\nocorr}\textsubscript{1}.
